IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: Maintenance of Town Gardens and Beautification Projects and Maintenance of Lee Garden
IRS990.MissionDesc: Beautification of the Town of New Canaan, Connecticut
IRS990.Desc: Civic Beautification - NCBL maintains 30 triangles in town, planters at Town Hall, a variety of plants at other locations. NCBL also provides over 225 hanging flower baskets for the downtown area and miscellaneous other projects to beautify New Canaan.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: Lee Garden - Lee Garden is a 2 acre garden with a large variety of azaleas and rhododendrons, plus a variety of other plants, with trails through the garden. It is open for public viewing from dawn to dusk.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: Membership Programs and Services - NCBL arranges educational speakers on various horticultural subjects to assist members in their beautification activities.

Form990PartVIISectionAGrp.TitleTxt: Director, Vice President of Civic Beautification

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: All Board members receive an electronic copy of the 990 before it is filed, and it is reviewed by the Executive Committee, which includes the Presidents, Vice President, Secretary, Treasurer, Vice President of Civic Beautification, and a representative from the Lee Garden Committee

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Available upon request by any person. Request may be made in person or by email to any officer.
